  section#personas
    h2 The customers: the office worker, the tourist, the social butterfly
    .text-flow-columns
      p Clientele to Lindt cafes vary with location, with the majority being locals (John, the office worker) or passers by (Michelle, the tourist). The exception is Sarah, who visits with her friends for special occasions.
      p These customers are middle class and socially conservative, appreciating Lindt's heritage and quality.
    figure
      figcaption Figure 2: Three main types of customer to the Lindt cafes.
      img src='/images/portfolio/personas.png' alt="The time-poor office worker, brand loving tourist and social butterfly."

  section#pain-points
    h2 The pain points: awareness and payment friction
    .text-flow-columns
      p We prioritised customers' pain points, identified during the research, using a severity matrix.
      p Raising awareness would increase customers, reducing payment friction would reduce queues and improve the customer experience.
    figure
      figcaption Figure 3: Severity matrix identifies customers' key pain points.
      img src='/images/portfolio/venn.png' alt="A venn diagram with pain points grouped into 3 overlapping circles: severe, frequent and easy to fix. The key pain points within all three circles were: findability, awareness of cafes' existence and location, awareness of menu range, queues. Physical payment was frequent and easy to fix, so it is highlighted."

